<span style="font-family:Whisper; font-size:50px; letter-spacing:3px;"> <center> Where... Where am I now? </center> </span>


<span style="font-family:Whisper; font-size:40px; letter-spacing:3px;"> <center> Another [[Level_List|hell]], right? </center> </span>


<div class="logo_img hoverimg-dim">[[File:intentar.png|center|570x570px|link=]]</div>


<span style="font-family:Whisper; font-size:23px; letter-spacing:3px;"> <center> My vision... it keeps shifting without stopping. The colors keep changing. One moment, I see something, and the next second, I see something else. </center> </span>


<span style="font-family:Whisper; font-size:20px; letter-spacing:3px;"> <center> As I walk, my surroundings shift. I'll look for somewhere to rest for a while. </center> </span>


{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
<div class="center">


I have spent quite a bit of time in this place. Maybe five days, or maybe ten days, or maybe 50 days, or maybe just two minutes. I found a [[The Frontrooms|"home."]] haha. It doesn't even look like a home to me, but like a house, a cave, and half a field! This place changes every time I look away. The colours go from loud, bright, and ugly to black, and there is something really wrong with the way everything looks! I don't even know... it looks disgusting!

I look gross. My hands are like this place!! I am becoming this place! Everything is so loud and bright and horribly ugly! There is no food here, and yet, I don’t have to eat. HELP ME!! GET ME OUT OF HERE!!!
Most of the time, I am relaxed and calm, but then, suddenly, it feels like I am hit upside the head or punched in the stomach, and dark thoughts overwhelm me. Each day I spend here, I feel worse, like my body is changing, breaking apart, becoming a part of this place. Sometimes, I feel faint and laugh nervously. I don't know how much more I can take.

It makes me feel like running for hours non-stop, it makes me want to laugh for no good reason, and cry. My heart is racing, then stops completely. Also, there is a moment when a cold breeze is blowing through me, then a hot one. It's very disconcerting to me; what's wrong with this place? It's the worst place I've ever been to. Out of all [[Level List|the hells]] that I could be in, this place is by far the worst. Pure torture. I want to lie down and rest, but I can't find a place to do that.

I keep getting flashes; hands are pointing at me, I hear laughing, sounds, colors, someone looking at me...and there I am. But then again, I can't find anything.

<span style="font-family:Whisper; font-size:50px; letter-spacing:3px;"> <center> Hurts </center> </span>

<div class="logo_img hoverimg-dim">[[File:3dblood.png|center|570x570px|link=]]</div>


I have no idea about my mental state right now. This place has driven me so crazy, I've cried. What if I did something horrible to [[A.A.E.G.|justify]] my exile? I had an almost-death experience when at [[Level 883]], but I got out of that one by pure luck. Then I went to a thousand more places and almost got killed. Now here I am...And thinking, What if I can't do it this time? What if I die? What if that was what I was meant to do? Laugh, haha, I must sound crazy! All I can do is run, laugh. This place made me feel like I was going insane. It's not just where I'm currently at, but everywhere I've been before, as well as every person I've interacted with. I am just a nobody, and I'm a nobody. I deserved better than the life that I've lived, but I am now. I've created and earned the right to die, just not in this manner. There was no justice there in life or after. There's just pain.

Every single day, the situation only continues to worsen...and the end result is pain...

There is absolutely no escape from this situation. There isn't. There is nothing or no one who could get me out of this place. Even if I were to scream for help, they would ignore me... as much as nobody else would. I wander through endless corridors, but they all lead to the same stop. I wander through great mountains and huge numbers and words spoken and sayings learned... all are places of nothing.

Hahahhahah... I am getting crazier every day. I cannot understand anything. It feels awful, awful, awful, awful, awful, awful, awful. Every part of me feels awful, and I do not know why. I cannot inflict pain on myself. My blood is all solid and all gel and all vapour, and it doesn't exist—it vanishes. I cannot run, I can only walk. I cannot laugh, I can only scream. Did you see that? It changed locations. And wait... look... another change.

<span style="font-family:Whisper; font-size:50px; letter-spacing:3px;"> <center> It's Funny. </center> </span>

<div class="logo_img hoverimg-dim">[[File:Funny..png|center|570x570px|link=]]</div>


I’m realising more and more how slowly I’m dying, as I look for ways to escape this hellhole. There’s just not much I can say or think about being here anymore. I’m not even sure where I stand with people. Do people see me as perfect or not? I know that no matter what I do, I try my best to impress them, but there’s always some little thing that they will find to criticise me for. Whether it was something good or bad, it could have been that they saw someone "better" than me doing something worse, and then they praised the output. That was my situation, and it was very painful to go through. It was detrimental to me and broke my spirit.

It’s funny how hypocritical people (Including myself) are, in many ways. I mean, I complain about thousands of things, but when I do them, no one can stop me. Why? Because I’m a bad person. Because what I’m doing is basically just searching my own soul for a very long time, searching and searching and searching, hoping that I will find something within myself to soothe the pain of the endless searching.

I cannot do it; there are things that have been very painful for me, and I do not know how to think about them. Some people enjoy experiencing pain, while I believe I enjoyed having power. I do not understand how someone may prefer to experience pain over having power; however, there are many people who do. I continue forward; I continue to walk and to ramble in my head because that is the only thing I am capable of doing. I cannot create. I will never accomplish anything. I am perpetually a catastrophe for everyone around me, and every time I think I have created something useful or valuable, it is nothing more than trash to me — I know that it is trash. I am trash.

I want to run away from this place and leave immediately. However, every time there is a change, even if it is just a small change, it causes me great pain, and every time it hurts. It is somewhat humorous that every change causes me pain. Nevertheless, I have learned to escape this Level...

